cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel self-paced learning algorithm for domain adaptation in object detection, which involves training a model on a source domain and applying it to a target domain. This problem is related to transfer learning (cs.LG) and domain adaptation (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of Cycle-GAN, which is a popular method for image-to-image translation (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves experiments on cross-domain benchmarks, which is related to robotics (cs.RO) as object detection is an important task in robotics applications.
